## 2. COST CONTROL — Don't let the bill humble you (Source 2)

> Specifically Supabase, but the patterns apply to any DB/host (Vercel, etc.).
> Audit AFTER AI scaffolds your project — it defaults to inefficient patterns.

### 2.1 Efficient queries
- [ ] **Never `SELECT *`** by default. Select only the columns you need.
      AI scaffolding pulls every column, every image, every blob → you pay for
      all those reads/writes.
- [ ] Don't over-fetch rows; paginate and filter at the DB, not in app code.

### 2.2 Indexes
- [ ] Add indexes on columns you filter/search/join on. Without them the DB
      scans every row ("reading every name in the phone book"). Fine at 10 users,
      brutal at 1,000+.
- [ ] Use `get_advisors` (performance) to find missing indexes.

### 2.3 Connections
- [ ] Reuse connections / use a pooler. Don't open a new DB connection per page
      and leave it open — idle connections eat bandwidth and money.
- [ ] Close/clean up listeners and realtime subscriptions on unmount.

### 2.4 Storage hygiene
- [ ] Clean the "storage graveyard": delete test uploads, failed-signup artifacts,
      and duplicate/retry uploads. You pay rent on every orphaned object monthly.
- [ ] Add lifecycle cleanup for temp/unreferenced files.

### 2.5 Background jobs & logs
- [ ] No job silently retrying in a loop thousands of times. **Read the logs**
      (`get_logs`) regularly. Add retry caps + dead-letter handling + alerts.

### Cost ship-gate
1. No `SELECT *` in hot paths; columns scoped.
2. Indexes on all filter/search/join columns (`get_advisors` perf clean).
3. Connection pooling; no leaked subscriptions.
4. Storage cleaned of orphans; lifecycle rules set.
5. Logs reviewed; no runaway retry loops.

